    <a name="583"></a>
    
    <div id="answer-583" class="answer">
        
        <table>
        <tr>
        <td class="votecell">
            
<div class="vote">
    <input type="hidden" value="583">
    <a class="vote-up-off" title="This answer is useful (click again to undo)">up vote</a>
    <span class="vote-count-post">32</span>
    <a class="vote-down-off" title="This answer is not useful (click again to undo)">down vote</a>

</div>

        </td>
        <td>
            <div class="post-text"><p>In any Finder window or Open/Save dialog, you can hit <kbd>Command</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>G</kbd> to get a location bar from which you can directly type in the directory to go to. It even supports <code>~</code> for home and tab completion.</p>
</div>
