        <td>
            <div class="post-text"><h1>Image Wells</h1>

<p>All good mac programs contain image wells for opening files, such as the Desktop and Screen Saver pane in System Preferences:<br>
<img src="http://i.imgur.com/dPyCB.png" alt="alt text"></p>

<p>or in Filemerge:<br>
<img src="http://i.imgur.com/g8yFt.png" alt="alt text"></p>

<p>This nifty litte things allow you to drag-and-drop files into them (and in some cases, out of) to load them into the program. Here, I am changing the wallpaper by dragging the file out of Finder and into the image well:<br>
<img src="http://i.imgur.com/iXZsw.png" alt="alt text"></p>
</div>
            <table class="fw">
            <tr>
            <td class="vt">
                <div class="post-menu"><a href="/questions/400/mac-os-x-hidden-features-and-nice-tips-tricks/1589#1589" title="permalink to this answer">link</a><span class="lsep">|</span><a id="flag-post-1589" title="flag this post for serious problems or moderator attention">flag</a></div>
                
            </td>
            
            <td align="right" class="post-signature">
