    <a name="3193"></a>
    
    <div id="answer-3193" class="answer">
        
        <table>
        <tr>
        <td class="votecell">
            
<div class="vote">
    <input type="hidden" value="3193">
    <a class="vote-up-off" title="This answer is useful (click again to undo)">up vote</a>
    <span class="vote-count-post">5</span>
    <a class="vote-down-off" title="This answer is not useful (click again to undo)">down vote</a>

</div>

        </td>
        <td>
            <div class="post-text"><p>Needed this today, when i had to shut down serval macs.</p>

<p><kbd>ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>alt</kbd> + <kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>eject</kbd>   <strong>Shuts the computer down</strong></p>

<p><kbd>alt</kbd> + <kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>eject</kbd>    send it to <strong>sleep</strong></p>

<p><kbd>ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>eject</kbd>    <strong>restarts</strong> the Mac</p>

<p><kbd>alt</kbd> + <kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>esc</kbd>    let's you <strong>kill not responding programs</strong> (including the Finder)</p>

<p>and one of my favorites</p>

<p><kbd>⌘</kbd> + <kbd>,</kbd> gets you to <strong>preferences</strong> of almost every program</p>
</div>
            <table class="fw">
            <tr>
            <td class="vt">
